1
00:00:16,840 --> 00:00:18,080
Young Master Zhao...

2
00:00:18,080 --> 00:00:19,080
Young Master Zhao's here.

3
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:35,860
=Cases Between Us=

4
00:00:35,980 --> 00:00:38,940
=Episode 10=

5
00:00:47,760 --> 00:00:48,640
It's a murder.

6
00:00:50,120 --> 00:00:51,440
The victim was strangled.

7
00:00:56,760 --> 00:00:57,720
And you are?

8
00:00:58,040 --> 00:01:00,960
Special Investigative Consultant
to the Jingshi Police Department.

9
00:01:02,520 --> 00:01:03,600
Zhao Shaoshang.

10
00:01:06,080 --> 00:01:07,240
Investigative Consultant, eh?

11
00:01:07,968 --> 00:01:09,040
The proof isn't ready yet.

12
00:01:09,040 --> 00:01:09,800
They're printing it.

13
00:01:09,800 --> 00:01:10,840
If you don't believe me,

14
00:01:10,840 --> 00:01:11,880
ask your commissioner.

15
00:01:14,480 --> 00:01:15,120
Yang Dezhi.

16
00:01:16,560 --> 00:01:17,480
Brief me on the case.

17
00:01:20,240 --> 00:01:20,920
Yang Dezhi.

18
00:01:21,240 --> 00:01:21,760
Yes, sir.

19
00:01:22,080 --> 00:01:23,800
Clear everyone who doesn't belong here.

20
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:25,400
Yes, sir.

21
00:01:26,112 --> 00:01:27,040
Young Master Zhao,

22
00:01:27,040 --> 00:01:27,560
look.

23
00:01:27,560 --> 00:01:28,280
I...

24
00:01:28,880 --> 00:01:29,520
What is this?

25
00:01:30,680 --> 00:01:31,560
What do you mean?

26
00:01:32,440 --> 00:01:34,720
Another murder!

27
00:01:34,880 --> 00:01:35,560
Let go.

28
00:01:39,920 --> 00:01:44,720
Division Four Chief is wary of
the newly appointed consultant.

29
00:01:44,720 --> 00:01:49,160
Police infighting at the murder scene.

30
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:50,200
Young Lady Zhao.

31
00:01:51,040 --> 00:01:51,560
Chief Yuan.

32
00:01:51,920 --> 00:01:52,440
Chief Yuan.

33
00:01:52,440 --> 00:01:53,280
I'll handle this.

34
00:01:54,144 --> 00:01:55,320
I'll take care of it.

35
00:01:57,320 --> 00:01:58,200
Young Lady Zhao,

36
00:01:58,440 --> 00:01:59,680
you must be joking.

37
00:02:00,440 --> 00:02:02,040
We're all friends here.

38
00:02:03,480 --> 00:02:04,160
Friends.

39
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:06,200
Friends.

40
00:02:06,320 --> 00:02:07,240
We're all friends.

41
00:02:07,280 --> 00:02:08,280
Sorry about that.

42
00:02:13,320 --> 00:02:14,120
Chief Yuan,

43
00:02:14,720 --> 00:02:15,840
may I have a word with you?

44
00:02:22,280 --> 00:02:22,760
Speak.

45
00:02:23,200 --> 00:02:25,480
The commissioner asked me
to pass along a message.

46
00:02:26,200 --> 00:02:27,760
Young Master Zhao
has just taken the job.

47
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:30,400
He hopes you'll look after him.

48
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:30,960
Then tell

49
00:02:30,960 --> 00:02:33,240
the commissioner this.

50
00:02:33,240 --> 00:02:34,400
Next time I arrest someone,

51
00:02:34,640 --> 00:02:36,000
don't release them

52
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:37,360
without my permission.

53
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:42,600
Chief Cao.

54
00:02:43,664 --> 00:02:45,280
See you at Tiansheng Restaurant tonight.

55
00:02:45,280 --> 00:02:46,760
Sure. I'll leave you to it.

56
00:02:47,560 --> 00:02:47,920
I'm off.

57
00:02:48,320 --> 00:02:48,880
See you.

58
00:02:51,640 --> 00:02:52,960
Exclusive report for Ta Kung Pao.

59
00:02:52,976 --> 00:02:53,936
Take the picture.

60
00:02:54,440 --> 00:02:55,080
Yang Dezhi,

61
00:02:55,960 --> 00:02:56,600
go ahead.

62
00:03:00,200 --> 00:03:01,200
The victim is

63
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:02,880
Lu Ruiheng. Thirty-three years old.

64
00:03:03,280 --> 00:03:03,960
Unemployed.

65
00:03:04,520 --> 00:03:06,120
Lived off the family fortune.

66
00:03:06,192 --> 00:03:08,400
His grandfather was
Deputy Salt Distribution Commissioner.

67
00:03:08,680 --> 00:03:09,840
Did you know him?

68
00:03:10,240 --> 00:03:11,280
I'd heard of him,

69
00:03:11,480 --> 00:03:12,440
but never met him.

70
00:03:13,320 --> 00:03:14,000
Married.

71
00:03:14,440 --> 00:03:15,200
No children.

72
00:03:15,440 --> 00:03:16,920
An arranged marriage.

73
00:03:17,280 --> 00:03:18,640
They weren't close.

74
00:03:19,440 --> 00:03:20,040
Go on.

75
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:22,600
The victim was 1.85 meters tall

76
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:24,960
and weighed nearly eighty kilograms.

77
00:03:24,960 --> 00:03:27,240
According to Chief Yuan,

78
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:28,800
whoever hoisted the body into the tree

79
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:29,400
must have been

80
00:03:29,400 --> 00:03:31,600
even heavier than the victim.

81
00:03:32,440 --> 00:03:33,440
Strangled first,

82
00:03:33,880 --> 00:03:34,720
and then hung up.

83
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:37,240
As for the rest,

84
00:03:37,240 --> 00:03:38,760
Chief Yuan hadn't said yet.

85
00:03:39,120 --> 00:03:40,320
Chief Yuan,

86
00:03:40,840 --> 00:03:42,440
don't tell me you couldn't see this.

87
00:03:44,200 --> 00:03:45,880
If he'd been strangled,

88
00:03:45,980 --> 00:03:46,720
the ligature mark

89
00:03:46,784 --> 00:03:48,960
would run horizontally
toward the back of the neck.

90
00:03:48,960 --> 00:03:49,960
But this one

91
00:03:49,960 --> 00:03:51,160
starts above the Adam's apple

92
00:03:51,160 --> 00:03:53,080
and angles up behind both ears.

93
00:03:53,080 --> 00:03:54,960
Didn't our
special investigative consultant

94
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:56,520
study forensic science?

95
00:03:57,600 --> 00:03:59,000
The victim's face is clean.

96
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:00,600
No signs of a struggle.

97
00:04:00,760 --> 00:04:02,360
What? You think someone hung him up

98
00:04:02,360 --> 00:04:03,600
and he just died like that?

99
00:04:03,800 --> 00:04:05,840
Was the killer incredibly strong?

100
00:04:06,560 --> 00:04:08,000
Just because you're weak

101
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:09,560
doesn't mean everyone else is.

102
00:04:10,560 --> 00:04:12,120
His cervical spine was broken.

103
00:04:12,120 --> 00:04:13,640
The upper vertebrae were dislocated.

104
00:04:13,880 --> 00:04:15,000
If the rope was tight enough

105
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:16,960
and the pull
was sharp enough, like this.

106
00:04:19,520 --> 00:04:20,680
Snap, and he's dead.

107
00:04:21,480 --> 00:04:22,600
Get off my face.

108
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:28,320
I'm going up.

109
00:04:29,440 --> 00:04:30,600
I'm going, too.

110
00:04:30,600 --> 00:04:31,640
What are you going up for?

111
00:04:31,680 --> 00:04:32,680
What are you going up for?

112
00:04:32,680 --> 00:04:33,680
I'm a cop.

113
00:04:33,680 --> 00:04:34,600
I'm covering the story.

114
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:35,400
Give me a break.

115
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:36,816
If you fall, I'll take care of you.

116
00:04:37,760 --> 00:04:38,280
Young Master.

117
00:04:39,808 --> 00:04:41,360
- Hold the ladder steady.
- Careful.

118
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:52,480
Chief.

119
00:04:53,080 --> 00:04:53,800
Chief.

120
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:55,200
We found him.

121
00:04:58,840 --> 00:04:59,480
It's him.

122
00:05:04,520 --> 00:05:05,328
Officer.

123
00:05:05,344 --> 00:05:07,136
Did you give
Young Master Lu a ride last night?

124
00:05:07,360 --> 00:05:07,920
I did.

125
00:05:08,760 --> 00:05:09,200
What time?

126
00:05:09,200 --> 00:05:10,360
Where did he get in?

127
00:05:10,360 --> 00:05:11,232
Why did he come here?

128
00:05:11,320 --> 00:05:12,320
Just after midnight.

129
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:14,320
He got in on Yanzhi Alley.

130
00:05:14,320 --> 00:05:15,232
I dropped him off here

131
00:05:15,400 --> 00:05:16,480
and left right away.

132
00:05:17,080 --> 00:05:19,120
What happened after that...

133
00:05:19,360 --> 00:05:20,320
I don't know.

134
00:05:23,480 --> 00:05:24,280
Really?

135
00:05:25,370 --> 00:05:26,000
Actually...

136
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:28,360
Actually, a pretty young lady came to me

137
00:05:28,680 --> 00:05:29,920
and gave me three silver coins

138
00:05:30,200 --> 00:05:31,360
to wait outside

139
00:05:31,360 --> 00:05:32,280
a pleasure house

140
00:05:32,480 --> 00:05:34,080
and make sure I picked up
Young Master Lu

141
00:05:34,080 --> 00:05:35,400
and brought him to Baishu Street.

142
00:05:35,728 --> 00:05:36,680
Which pleasure house?

143
00:05:38,096 --> 00:05:39,408
When the police ask questions,

144
00:05:39,480 --> 00:05:41,200
you can ignore anyone else.

145
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:45,800
Which pleasure house?

146
00:05:46,560 --> 00:05:47,560
It was two grass radicals.

147
00:05:48,160 --> 00:05:49,200
I can't read.

148
00:05:49,840 --> 00:05:50,920
Where did he get out?

149
00:05:51,920 --> 00:05:52,560
Right there.

150
00:05:55,120 --> 00:05:56,800
Do you remember
what the woman looked like?

151
00:05:57,040 --> 00:05:58,440
She had a hat and a scarf.

152
00:05:58,440 --> 00:05:59,520
I couldn't see her face.

153
00:05:59,960 --> 00:06:02,000
But she looked like a rich young lady.

154
00:06:02,440 --> 00:06:03,560
I figured

155
00:06:03,560 --> 00:06:05,520
she'd be one
of Young Master Lu's old flames.

156
00:06:07,040 --> 00:06:07,480
Oh, right.

157
00:06:07,840 --> 00:06:09,120
I heard him say

158
00:06:09,400 --> 00:06:10,680
"Qiao'er".

159
00:06:10,920 --> 00:06:12,160
Must've been her name.

160
00:06:13,360 --> 00:06:14,080
Officer,

161
00:06:14,520 --> 00:06:15,920
I've told you everything I know.

162
00:06:16,160 --> 00:06:17,480
I won't be held responsible

163
00:06:17,920 --> 00:06:19,280
for anything after this, right?

164
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:20,160
You won't.

165
00:06:20,160 --> 00:06:20,800
Thanks.

166
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:22,440
Hold on.

167
00:06:23,280 --> 00:06:24,520
Take us to Yanzhi Alley.

168
00:06:24,576 --> 00:06:26,000
The place where you picked him up.

169
00:06:29,880 --> 00:06:31,680
The Eight Alleys are a maze.

170
00:06:31,744 --> 00:06:33,360
Do you think you
can find it without him?

171
00:06:34,480 --> 00:06:38,200
Or are you familiar with the place,
Chief Yuan?

172
00:06:42,384 --> 00:06:43,240
I'm coming, too.

173
00:06:43,600 --> 00:06:45,840
You are not. What will people think
if they see you there?

174
00:06:45,840 --> 00:06:46,640
That's ridiculous.

175
00:06:46,640 --> 00:06:48,270
Father will blame me.
I can't handle that.

176
00:06:48,280 --> 00:06:48,680
Let's go.

177
00:06:49,160 --> 00:06:51,240
But I haven't gotten a fare all morning.

178
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:55,880
Where's my wallet?

179
00:06:58,800 --> 00:07:00,080
Why are you taking it again?

180
00:07:01,040 --> 00:07:01,880
Can I come?

181
00:07:04,400 --> 00:07:05,000
Let's go.

182
00:07:06,080 --> 00:07:07,520
You stay here.

183
00:07:07,720 --> 00:07:08,720
Zhao Cai, give me my coat.

184
00:07:10,240 --> 00:07:11,120
I'll fill you in later.

185
00:07:13,040 --> 00:07:14,120
I haven't gotten in yet.

186
00:07:27,760 --> 00:07:28,440
Here it is, sir.

187
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:32,920
Do you know how to read this?

188
00:07:33,460 --> 00:07:37,280
(Handan Pleasure House)

189
00:07:37,280 --> 00:07:38,080
Handan.

190
00:07:39,360 --> 00:07:40,240
Lotus.

191
00:07:40,880 --> 00:07:43,520
Back in the Yin and Zhou dynasties,
it was called fuyao

192
00:07:43,800 --> 00:07:45,120
or pundarika.

193
00:07:45,800 --> 00:07:48,080
Cao Zhi wrote On Lotus.

194
00:07:49,160 --> 00:07:51,280
"Among all blooming flowers,

195
00:07:52,360 --> 00:07:55,640
none surpasses this one."

196
00:07:55,640 --> 00:07:57,500
(Handan Pleasure House)

197
00:08:00,120 --> 00:08:01,360
How do you say this in English?

198
00:08:04,760 --> 00:08:05,840
Lotus.

199
00:08:06,840 --> 00:08:07,440
French?

200
00:08:07,880 --> 00:08:08,360
German?

201
00:08:08,360 --> 00:08:09,120
Italian?

202
00:08:09,168 --> 00:08:11,104
What order and family
does the lotus belong to?

203
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:14,320
Like you know.

204
00:08:14,320 --> 00:08:17,960
Lotus.

205
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:20,760
Proteales. Nelumbonaceae.

206
00:08:22,440 --> 00:08:23,200
Do you know

207
00:08:23,200 --> 00:08:24,440
the different varieties?

208
00:08:24,440 --> 00:08:25,760
Blushing Face, Spring on the Desk,

209
00:08:25,760 --> 00:08:26,420
and Tipsy Fairy.

210
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:28,880
Do you know how those names came about?

211
00:08:29,840 --> 00:08:30,840
Compete with me?

212
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:33,160
I read a lot.

213
00:08:38,520 --> 00:08:39,720
I'll smack you with my fan.

214
00:08:40,320 --> 00:08:42,400
Listen. If you want
to keep yourself safe,

215
00:08:42,400 --> 00:08:43,160
shut your mouth.

216
00:08:43,160 --> 00:08:43,800
Got it?

217
00:08:45,216 --> 00:08:46,160
What are you looking at?

218
00:08:46,160 --> 00:08:46,880
Get inside.

219
00:08:50,360 --> 00:08:50,800
Get inside!

220
00:08:54,080 --> 00:08:55,200
I was wondering

221
00:08:55,200 --> 00:08:56,520
why this place suddenly lit up.

222
00:08:56,520 --> 00:08:58,880
Turns out we've got honored guests.

223
00:08:59,360 --> 00:09:00,040
You see,

224
00:09:00,096 --> 00:09:01,296
it's still daylight.

225
00:09:01,328 --> 00:09:02,760
We haven't opened for business yet.

226
00:09:02,760 --> 00:09:03,640
Lu Ruiheng is dead.

227
00:09:03,640 --> 00:09:04,440
Did you know?

228
00:09:09,800 --> 00:09:10,880
I heard.

229
00:09:16,120 --> 00:09:17,400
Don't just stand out here.

230
00:09:17,400 --> 00:09:19,000
Please come inside.

231
00:09:23,360 --> 00:09:24,600
Here's what happened

232
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:26,520
last night.

233
00:09:26,880 --> 00:09:28,760
Young Lady Xiaoman and I

234
00:09:28,760 --> 00:09:30,360
watched Young Master Lu

235
00:09:30,360 --> 00:09:32,240
get into a rickshaw with our own eyes.

236
00:09:32,840 --> 00:09:34,720
Whatever happened after that

237
00:09:34,720 --> 00:09:36,520
had nothing to do with me.

238
00:09:36,880 --> 00:09:37,960
I swear before

239
00:09:37,960 --> 00:09:39,680
the Goddess Guanyin,

240
00:09:39,680 --> 00:09:41,000
I haven't hidden a single thing

241
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:42,240
from you.

242
00:09:45,040 --> 00:09:45,800
Where's Xiaoman?

243
00:09:47,640 --> 00:09:48,560
Don't even mention it.

244
00:09:48,760 --> 00:09:50,360
That poor girl's scared out of her wits.

245
00:09:50,640 --> 00:09:51,560
She's running a fever.

246
00:09:51,840 --> 00:09:53,120
If you want to question her,

247
00:09:53,184 --> 00:09:54,160
come back in a few days.

248
00:09:58,880 --> 00:09:59,880
Do you have a girl here

249
00:09:59,880 --> 00:10:00,920
named Qiao'er?

250
00:10:03,320 --> 00:10:04,600
Qiao'er?

251
00:10:05,560 --> 00:10:06,600
We did.

252
00:10:08,040 --> 00:10:09,520
But she hanged herself

253
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:11,040
half a month ago.

254
00:10:14,920 --> 00:10:15,640
She hanged herself?

255
00:10:17,280 --> 00:10:18,080
Let me explain.

256
00:10:18,080 --> 00:10:19,120
I didn't force her.

257
00:10:19,840 --> 00:10:21,520
I treated her well.

258
00:10:21,520 --> 00:10:22,080
Why wasn't this

259
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:23,760
reported to the police?

260
00:10:31,880 --> 00:10:33,000
Well,

261
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:34,960
she died the very first night

262
00:10:34,960 --> 00:10:35,920
she arrived.

263
00:10:35,920 --> 00:10:36,960
Technically,

264
00:10:37,200 --> 00:10:38,600
she wasn't one of our girls yet.

265
00:10:39,080 --> 00:10:39,680
You see,

266
00:10:39,680 --> 00:10:40,320
I figured

267
00:10:40,320 --> 00:10:42,280
the less trouble, the better.

268
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:43,560
So I didn't report it.

269
00:10:43,560 --> 00:10:44,520
It's not too late

270
00:10:45,040 --> 00:10:45,920
to report it now.

271
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:48,080
Look,

272
00:10:48,320 --> 00:10:48,840
you know what?

273
00:10:48,840 --> 00:10:51,160
Her family sent her here.

274
00:10:51,160 --> 00:10:52,480
Young Master Lu fell for her

275
00:10:52,480 --> 00:10:53,760
at first sight.

276
00:10:53,920 --> 00:10:55,080
He threw banquets,

277
00:10:55,320 --> 00:10:56,480
hired opera performers,

278
00:10:56,480 --> 00:10:57,080
and spent

279
00:10:57,080 --> 00:10:58,720
seventy or eighty taels
of silver on her.

280
00:10:58,720 --> 00:11:00,240
And what did she do?

281
00:11:00,240 --> 00:11:01,560
She pulled a long face,

282
00:11:01,560 --> 00:11:03,720
and then hanged herself.

283
00:11:03,720 --> 00:11:06,440
Poor Young Master Lu
was scared half to death.

284
00:11:07,232 --> 00:11:09,440
Sounds like Young Master Lu spent
quite a fortune on her.

285
00:11:10,352 --> 00:11:12,080
Qiao'er was a virgin courtesan,
wasn't she?

286
00:11:16,480 --> 00:11:18,160
By the rules of the Eight Alleys,

287
00:11:18,400 --> 00:11:20,360
there had to be a banquet, gold gifts,

288
00:11:21,440 --> 00:11:22,640
and celebration money.

289
00:11:22,672 --> 00:11:24,040
How much ended up in your pocket?

290
00:11:28,600 --> 00:11:29,640
Come on.

291
00:11:29,640 --> 00:11:31,400
It wasn't that much.

292
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:32,440
Celebration money?

293
00:11:35,480 --> 00:11:36,920
The so-called celebration money

294
00:11:37,560 --> 00:11:40,160
was a payoff to everyone, from the madam

295
00:11:40,160 --> 00:11:41,560
to every worker in the house.

296
00:11:41,920 --> 00:11:42,720
They'd all pitch in

297
00:11:43,640 --> 00:11:45,040
to send an unwilling virgin courtesan

298
00:11:45,800 --> 00:11:47,920
into the patron's room.

299
00:11:51,720 --> 00:11:52,440
Unwilling?

300
00:11:53,280 --> 00:11:54,280
How did they make her go?

301
00:11:59,720 --> 00:12:00,400
Threats.

302
00:12:01,640 --> 00:12:02,360
Drugging her.

303
00:12:03,824 --> 00:12:05,400
As long as the money was good enough,

304
00:12:05,440 --> 00:12:07,184
there wasn't a woman
they couldn't force.

305
00:12:12,080 --> 00:12:13,520
That's rape.

306
00:12:14,880 --> 00:12:15,920
Look,

307
00:12:16,640 --> 00:12:18,320
if she were a respectable young woman,

308
00:12:18,400 --> 00:12:19,080
then yes.

309
00:12:19,320 --> 00:12:20,480
That would be rape.

310
00:12:20,800 --> 00:12:22,520
But Qiao'er wasn't.

311
00:12:22,640 --> 00:12:25,080
She signed a contract
selling herself to my house.

312
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:28,176
Once you've entered a brothel, you
can't pretend to be a virtuous woman.

313
00:12:28,640 --> 00:12:30,120
That's not how it works.

314
00:12:39,080 --> 00:12:40,080
Did her parents

315
00:12:41,280 --> 00:12:42,200
sell her here?

316
00:12:43,320 --> 00:12:45,000
Her parents died young.

317
00:12:45,920 --> 00:12:47,160
Her aunt brought her here.

318
00:12:47,560 --> 00:12:48,320
Her aunt?

319
00:12:49,472 --> 00:12:50,480
Is she still in Beijing?

320
00:12:50,560 --> 00:12:51,872
She's from out of town.

321
00:12:53,040 --> 00:12:54,600
I heard she
left Beijing a long time ago.

322
00:13:04,740 --> 00:13:06,960
(Handan Pleasure House)

323
00:13:06,960 --> 00:13:08,320
Take care, sirs.

324
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:25,600
What?

325
00:13:26,432 --> 00:13:28,360
Why do I feel like
something's off with you?

326
00:13:29,920 --> 00:13:30,880
You're imagining things.

327
00:13:32,912 --> 00:13:34,848
Since you heard about
what happened to Qiao'er,

328
00:13:34,864 --> 00:13:36,000
you've been acting strange.

329
00:13:36,160 --> 00:13:37,080
What's wrong with you?

330
00:13:37,080 --> 00:13:38,000
Why are you here?

331
00:13:38,624 --> 00:13:40,360
This isn't a place for you
to fool around.

332
00:13:40,816 --> 00:13:42,832
If you're not here
to investigate, head home then.

333
00:13:43,240 --> 00:13:44,880
I don't have time to babysit you.

334
00:13:45,920 --> 00:13:47,200
Who says I'm not investigating?

335
00:13:59,080 --> 00:13:59,920
Excuse me.

336
00:14:00,640 --> 00:14:01,720
Do you have a restroom?

337
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:04,680
Inside.

338
00:14:05,760 --> 00:14:06,360
Do you want to

339
00:14:06,520 --> 00:14:07,160
come, too?

340
00:14:07,744 --> 00:14:09,000
I can't hold it anymore.

341
00:14:27,280 --> 00:14:28,390
(Xidan Theater South Market)

342
00:14:28,400 --> 00:14:29,808
Narrow eyes. Short and stocky.

343
00:14:29,808 --> 00:14:31,296
(Madam Huang)
A mole at the corner of her mouth.

344
00:14:32,200 --> 00:14:33,360
Is this Qiao'er's aunt?

345
00:14:41,480 --> 00:14:42,280
What are you doing?

346
00:14:43,800 --> 00:14:44,720
There's a scent.

347
00:14:45,440 --> 00:14:46,160
It's a clue.

348
00:14:46,600 --> 00:14:47,520
Write it down.

349
00:15:13,440 --> 00:15:14,240
Sir,

350
00:15:15,040 --> 00:15:16,600
have you always had your stall here?

351
00:15:16,800 --> 00:15:17,440
Yes.

352
00:15:17,600 --> 00:15:18,480
I already paid.

353
00:15:21,400 --> 00:15:22,920
I want to ask about someone.

354
00:15:23,120 --> 00:15:24,280
Do you know Huang Erya?

355
00:15:24,920 --> 00:15:26,080
Narrow eyes,

356
00:15:26,080 --> 00:15:27,520
short, and a mole by her mouth.

357
00:15:29,360 --> 00:15:30,840
You mean that trafficker?

358
00:15:30,840 --> 00:15:31,840
She has a teenage boy.

359
00:15:32,520 --> 00:15:33,360
Trafficker?

360
00:15:35,600 --> 00:15:37,720
The police files list her occupation

361
00:15:37,720 --> 00:15:39,400
as an employment agent.

362
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:41,440
Employment agent?

363
00:15:41,840 --> 00:15:43,160
More like a human trafficker.

364
00:15:44,720 --> 00:15:46,200
Does she have a niece?

365
00:15:47,400 --> 00:15:48,960
Haven't heard that.

366
00:15:51,880 --> 00:15:52,480
Huang Erya

367
00:15:52,480 --> 00:15:54,720
couldn't be Qiao'er's aunt.

368
00:15:54,720 --> 00:15:56,360
She must be the trafficker who sold her.

369
00:15:59,680 --> 00:16:00,880
Do you know where they live?

370
00:16:01,216 --> 00:16:02,880
They used to live in
that one-story house.

371
00:16:03,800 --> 00:16:04,720
What about now?

372
00:16:04,920 --> 00:16:05,600
They're dead.

373
00:16:06,160 --> 00:16:07,080
Both of them.

374
00:16:27,480 --> 00:16:28,680
I read the case file.

375
00:16:29,600 --> 00:16:32,320
The room wasn't ventilated properly
while they were burning charcoal.

376
00:16:32,384 --> 00:16:34,176
When the neighbor came by
the next morning,

377
00:16:34,224 --> 00:16:35,344
they were already dead.

378
00:16:43,400 --> 00:16:44,560
I suspect it was murder.

379
00:16:46,192 --> 00:16:47,800
It had only just started getting cold.

380
00:16:47,808 --> 00:16:49,890
It's too early in the season
to be burning charcoal.

381
00:16:50,080 --> 00:16:51,160
And these houses are packed

382
00:16:51,160 --> 00:16:52,640
so close together. The walls are thin.

383
00:16:52,720 --> 00:16:54,304
Even if it was
carbon monoxide poisoning,

384
00:16:54,310 --> 00:16:55,790
as long as they were still conscious
and called for help,

385
00:16:55,800 --> 00:16:56,880
someone would've heard them.

386
00:16:57,920 --> 00:16:59,360
Who do you think the killer is?

387
00:17:00,680 --> 00:17:01,960
Whoever was avenging Qiao'er.

388
00:17:02,416 --> 00:17:03,640
It's probably the same person

389
00:17:03,640 --> 00:17:04,520
who killed Lu Ruiheng.

390
00:17:07,040 --> 00:17:07,720
Chief.

391
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:11,728
I don't think we'll be able
to find either of their bodies.

392
00:17:12,120 --> 00:17:12,680
Why not?

393
00:17:13,320 --> 00:17:13,840
Huang Erya

394
00:17:13,840 --> 00:17:15,600
was kidnapped here when she was young.

395
00:17:15,600 --> 00:17:16,848
No one could trace her family,

396
00:17:16,920 --> 00:17:19,160
so her body was sent to a mass grave.

397
00:17:20,040 --> 00:17:21,600
We can't find either body.

398
00:17:21,880 --> 00:17:22,760
What about Lu Ruiheng?

399
00:17:23,080 --> 00:17:24,480
Still nothing from the coroner?

400
00:17:26,800 --> 00:17:27,400
Let's go.

401
00:17:28,680 --> 00:17:29,280
Where to?

402
00:17:29,760 --> 00:17:30,520
Peking Union.

403
00:17:31,424 --> 00:17:33,680
If we wait for your coroner,
we'll be waiting forever.

404
00:17:34,240 --> 00:17:36,048
Du should be done
with the autopsy by now.

405
00:17:37,880 --> 00:17:38,880
I'll pay him this time.

406
00:17:40,680 --> 00:17:41,280
Young Master,

407
00:17:41,280 --> 00:17:42,280
I found something...

408
00:17:42,280 --> 00:17:43,040
Talk while we walk.

409
00:17:44,240 --> 00:17:45,120
Carry my coat.

410
00:17:55,800 --> 00:17:56,280
No drugs

411
00:17:56,280 --> 00:17:57,640
were found in his system.

412
00:17:57,712 --> 00:17:59,270
He had been drinking before he died,

413
00:17:59,280 --> 00:18:00,160
but not much.

414
00:18:00,920 --> 00:18:02,720
There were abrasions and bruises
on his arms,

415
00:18:04,080 --> 00:18:06,080
but those were only minor injuries
from a fall.

416
00:18:06,600 --> 00:18:08,840
The fatal injury
was to his cervical spine.

417
00:18:09,120 --> 00:18:11,040
The second vertebral arch was fractured.

418
00:18:13,040 --> 00:18:14,480
If he'd simply hanged himself,

419
00:18:14,480 --> 00:18:16,400
how could the vertebral arch
have been broken?

420
00:18:17,360 --> 00:18:19,160
Unless there was an enormous force

421
00:18:19,160 --> 00:18:20,360
applied at very high speed.

422
00:18:26,760 --> 00:18:28,920
That's what caused these deep marks.

423
00:18:30,560 --> 00:18:32,240
What could leave deep marks?

424
00:18:39,240 --> 00:18:40,640
A pulley system.

425
00:18:40,640 --> 00:18:43,720
(End of Episode 10)

426
00:18:45,201 --> 00:18:46,841
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

427
00:18:46,841 --> 00:18:48,381
♪Troubled times
are but a laughing matter♪

428
00:18:48,381 --> 00:18:49,631
♪However, the world changes♪

429
00:18:49,631 --> 00:18:51,551
♪You'll still be by my side♪

430
00:18:51,551 --> 00:18:53,241
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

431
00:18:53,241 --> 00:18:54,811
♪Praise and blame come and go♪

432
00:18:54,811 --> 00:18:56,381
♪If this is my final chapter♪

433
00:18:56,381 --> 00:18:58,881
♪I'll solve this mystery with you♪
